encodePublicKey

public byte[] encodePublicKey(java.security.PublicKey key)

Returns the encoded form of the designated Diffie-Hellman public key according to the Raw format supported by this library.

The Raw format for a DH public key, in this implementation, is a byte sequence consisting of the following:

  1. 4-byte magic consisting of the value of the literal Registry.MAGIC_RAW_DH_PUBLIC_KEY,
  3. 1-byte version consisting of the constant: 0x01,
  4. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter q in internet order,
  5. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the DH parameter q,
  6. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter p in internet order,
  7. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the DH parameter p,
  8. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter g,
  9. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the DH parameter g,
  10. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter y,
  11. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the DH parameter y,

Specified by:
encodePublicKey in interface IKeyPairCodec
Parameters:
key - the key to encode.
Returns:
the Raw format encoding of the designated key.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the designated key is not a DH one.
See Also:
Registry.MAGIC_RAW_DH_PUBLIC_KEY

Returns the encoded form of the designated Diffie-Hellman private key according to the Raw format supported by this library.

The Raw format for a DH private key, in this implementation, is a byte sequence consisting of the following:

  1. 4-byte magic consisting of the value of the literal Registry.MAGIC_RAW_DH_PRIVATE_KEY,
  3. 1-byte version consisting of the constant: 0x01,

  6. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter p in internet order,
  7. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the DH parameter p,
  8. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter g,
  9. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the DH parameter g,
  10. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the DH parameter x,
